          <msContents>
            <summary>Text praising the night of the full moon in the night of Pauṣa (December-January) along with the positive results derived from the rites and ceremonies (vrata) performed during that period, especially fasting. Presented as a conversation between the legendary king Yudhiṣṭhira and the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa who instructs the former on how to perform certain observances, such as the veneration of ancestors.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Pauṣākṛṣṇasaphalaikādaśīmahātmya</title>
              <title type="vernacular">पौषाकृष्णसफलैकादशीमहात्म्य</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Kāśīnātha</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīpadmapurāṇe pauṣākṛṣṇasaphalaikādaśīmahātm[ya]ṃ / saṃpurṇaṃ // svārthaṃ parārthi // kāśīnāthacāde kara[ṇa]likhitaṃ pauṣakṛṣṇa ekādaśīsaṃpūrṇaṃ // svārthāṃṣarārkṣāṃ // (f. 4v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
